        <updateDate>2009-07-23T22:28:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Transparent Markets Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to impose an excise tax on over-the-counter derivative transactions. Sets the rate of such tax at 0.25% of the fair market value of the underlying property with respect to, or the notional principal amount of, the derivative financial instrument involved in such transactions. Defines &quot;derivative financial instrument&quot; as any option, forward contract, short position, notional principal contract, credit default swap, or similar financial instrument in any share of corporate stock, interest in a widely held or publicly traded partnership or trust, debt instrument, commodity which is actively traded, foreign currency, or specified index. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
